# Shared build-context ignore for all images built with repo-root context (`.`):
#   - docker/bitcoin-node.Dockerfile -> the bitcoind node image
#   - docker/tools.Dockerfile        -> the three Rust tools
#   - docker/netem.Dockerfile        -> the P2P netem helper
#
# This file stays at the repo root because `.dockerignore` is scoped to the
# build-context root, not to the Dockerfile location.
#
# Allowlist only what those builds COPY; everything else (.git, and the Rust
# target/ dirs that reach GBs after local builds) stays out of the upload.
#
# Under BuildKit, docker/tools.Dockerfile.dockerignore overrides this file for
# the tools image. The classic builder ignores per-Dockerfile files, so this
# root file must still cover both images on its own — hence the Rust allowlist
# entries.
*
!docker/bitcoin-node.Dockerfile
!docker/entrypoint.sh
!docker/netem.Dockerfile
!docker/netem-entrypoint.sh
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
!.cargo
!crates
